      {
        "id": "4",
        "title": "Same values in registries for USB devices might mean different things depending on windows OS version"
      },
      {
        "id": "5",
        "title": "EMDMgmt and some logs store the VSN in decimal instead of hex"
      },
      {
        "id": "6",
        "title": "The VSN is the join key, found in LNK/Jump Lists, Shellbags, Event 1006, EMDMgmt"
      },
      {
        "id": "7",
        "title": "Windows update can clear USB evidence"
      },
